The paper deals with communication and distributed algorithms, which are common topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Distributed Computing (cs.DC), and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of hypergraphs and connectivity also suggests a possible fit in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the mention of linear programming and optimization techniques may indicate a connection to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
